{"author":{"id":"bf52274e4b8baa03d436abcc532c02b6a719b9a772a7e952e18fcc8627570e5f"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770775113,"nonce":"9SeYJuDQUGUxu42zSIn7d/g8nZA=","title":"Allow literals in scattered parameters","message":"Allow literals in scattered parameters. The question is where to stuff these literals into. Normally, we stuff them into the default values of command inputs. But, that won't work for scattered inputs because you're trying to stuff an array of values into a place that can only hold a value. Perhaps there's a way to stuff them in at the level of a workflow step.\n\nHere's a workflow that has a scattered literal, and should work but doesn't.\n```\n(define echo\n  (command #:inputs (message #:type string)\n           #:run \"echo\" message))\n\n(workflow ()\n  (scatter (echo)\n           #:message #(\"foo\")))\n```","files":null}]}